HEADWORD: Hereditable
<hw>He*red"i*ta*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>hereditabilis</ets>, fr. <ets>hereditare</ets> to inherit, fr. L.
<ets>hereditas</ets> heirship inheritance, <ets>heres</ets> heir: cf.
OF. <ets>hereditable</ets>. See <er>Heir</er>, and cf.
<er>Heritable</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of being inherited.
See <er>Inheritable</er>.</def> <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Qualified to inherit; capable of
inheriting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hereditably</ent>⟦br⟧
